[{"id":"VR024010","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents four isolated arrangements of charged spheres, labeled Arrangement A, Arrangement B, Arrangement C, and Arrangement D. Arrangement A shows two spheres, each with a charge of positive Q, located at a distance of r from one another. Arrangement B shows two spheres, each with a charge of positive Q, located at a distance of 2 r from one another. Arrangement C shows two spheres, one with a charge of positive Q and the other with a charge of negative Q, located at a distance of r from one another. Arrangement D shows two spheres, on with a charge of positive Q and the other with a charge of negative Q, located at a distance of 2 r from one another.\" height=\"198\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR024010.g01.png\" width=\"450\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Four isolated arrangements of charged spheres are created for an experiment, as shown above. Which of the following correctly compares the electric potential energy <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"U\"><math alttext=\"U\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>U</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> of the arrangements? Assume <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"U equals 0 \"><math alttext=\"U equals 0 \" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>U</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> when the charges are an infinite distance apart.</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR024010_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"U sub A is greater than U sub B, which is greater than U sub C, which is greater than U sub D\"><math alttext=\"U sub A is greater than U sub B, which is greater than U sub C, which is greater than U sub D\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>U</mi></mrow><mrow><mtext>A</mtext></mrow